-- Japan Exchange Group head sees major benefits for Japan from weak yen
-- By Takahiko Wada
-- Wed Sep 24, 2014 03:15AM EDT
-- None



TOKYO, Sept 24 (Reuters) - The head of financial exchange operator Japan Exchange Group Inc <8697.T> said on Wednesday that he sees major benefits for Japan overall from the weakening of the yen.

Atsushi Saito's comment followed the yen's slide to a six-year low of 109.46 versus the dollar last Friday. On Wednesday, the Japanese currency was trading around 108.65 to the greenback. [FRX/]